Select the best star that has the best fitness value as the black hole.
Change the location of each star according to Eq. (29).
If a star reaches a location with lower cost than the black hole, exchange their locations.
If a star crosses the event horizon of the black hole.
Calculate the Eq. (30).
When the distance between a candidate solution and the black hole (best candidate) is less than R, that candidate is collapsed and a new candidate is created and distributed randomly in the search space.
Replace it with a new star in a random location in the search space.
Else, break
If a termination criterion (a maximum number of iterations or a sufficiently good fitness) is met exit the loop.

The principal concept of the HHO approach is the participatory manners and a pursuit technique of a Harris hawk in nature, which is understood as a shock attack. The strategy is formed from the two major sections of the exploration and exploitation stages. The siege process consists of two phases, including the soft-siege (SS) and hard-siege (HS)36,37. The soft-siege relations are as follows:31Ht+1=Hrand-r1.Hrand-2r2.Htifq1≥0.5Hprey-Hmean-r3LB+r4UB-LBifq1≤0.5.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
